{
  "texts": [
    "They excel in adapting to diverse data types and tasks, particularly within supervised learning (SL) that depends on labeled data (Elhoseny et al. 2018; Guo et al. 2016).",
    "A hybrid model H operates by integrating the functionalities of its constituent models, which can be denoted as M 1 and M 2.",
    "The operation of H on an input x can be mathematically represented in two primary forms.",
    "In a sequential configuration, the output of the first model M 1 becomes the input for the second model M 2, formulated as:",
    "Alternatively, in a parallel configuration, the model processes input x through both M 1 and M 2 simultaneously, and their outputs are subsequently merged."
  ]
}